[The Demon Hunter's Romance]

2
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,990
[Episode 25]

3
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:48,070
Wang.

4
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:49,479
Wang.

5
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:50,840
Kuan.

6
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,000
Kuan.

7
00:01:53,350 --> 00:01:54,310
Next is…

8
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,170
Lu.

9
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:56,640
Lu.

10
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:57,680
Yi.

11
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,430
Yi.

12
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:00,350
Guang.

13
00:02:04,830 --> 00:02:05,560
Can you read?

14
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:06,350
Yes,

15
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,400
of course.

16
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:14,540
How do you pronounce this?

17
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:15,760
[Ganshan Clinic]

18
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:18,170
I think this means "walk."

19
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:19,560
I got it.

20
00:02:19,579 --> 00:02:20,510
This is "Gan."

21
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:22,870
This character looks like a mountain.

22
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:24,000
I know, it's "Shan."

23
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:26,640
-Ganshan Clinic.
-Ganshan Clinic.

24
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,710
Ganshan Clinic?

25
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:33,510
Where is Ganshan Clinic?

26
00:02:34,940 --> 00:02:36,060
In Shendu City.

27
00:02:37,630 --> 00:02:38,590
Shendu City?

28
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:50,020
Xuanye.

29
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:21,560
Xuanye?

30
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,750
Why are you drinking alone out here?

31
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:25,560
Feeling down?

32
00:03:27,630 --> 00:03:28,430
Drink with me.

33
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,280
I'll pass on the wine.

34
00:03:32,590 --> 00:03:34,510
I'm going back to the government office later.

35
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:35,930
I'll just chat with you for a bit.

36
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:37,590
I've been in a bad mood lately.

37
00:03:38,890 --> 00:03:39,520
Why?

38
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,329
Sima Lingying left,

39
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,490
and it upset you?

40
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,560
Her?

41
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,960
I wanted her gone.

42
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,720
You two like each other.

43
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,150
There's no one

44
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:52,140
and nothing

45
00:03:52,260 --> 00:03:53,720
standing between you two.

46
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,470
You should treasure

47
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:56,800
a connection like that.

48
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,960
If you really like her,

49
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:00,910
stop saying

50
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,000
hurtful things.

51
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:04,080
When she moves on,

52
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:06,040
you'll regret it.

53
00:04:06,570 --> 00:04:07,810
What makes you think

54
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:08,620
I like her?

55
00:04:09,710 --> 00:04:10,680
The Commissioner and I

56
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,750
are from different worlds.

57
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:13,410
How could I possibly like her?

58
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,550
You're too deep in it

59
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:17,779
to see clearly.

60
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:21,040
You mean,

61
00:04:21,829 --> 00:04:23,160
I don't even know

62
00:04:23,180 --> 00:04:23,920
who I like,

63
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,800
and an outsider like you

64
00:04:25,830 --> 00:04:27,390
knows better about my feelings

65
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:28,270
than I do?

66
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,070
So you don't like her?

67
00:04:34,659 --> 00:04:36,390
I don't want to talk about this.

68
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,750
Do you often think about

69
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:43,530
-what happened in the painting?
-Chief Chu.

70
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:46,840
Chief Chu.

71
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:48,240
A body was found in a well

72
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:49,510
during excavation in the north of the city.

73
00:04:49,510 --> 00:04:51,840
Lord Geng wants you to go there instantly.

74
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,040
Make way.

75
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,680
Official business, make way.

76
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,240
Make way.

77
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:03,810
Step back a bit.

78
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:08,020
It's usually peaceful around here.

79
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:08,390
It is?

80
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:08,870
No one

81
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:10,120
saw it coming.

82
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:12,560
Sir,

83
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,000
can you tell us

84
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:14,970
what's going on?

85
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,070
Enough. It has nothing to do

86
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:16,480
with you.

87
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,880
What a strange way to die.

88
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,000
Except for the skull,

89
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:21,760
all bones are shattered.

90
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,430
Looks like the victim

91
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,950
was run over…

92
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:28,090
by something massive.

93
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:32,630
Chief,

94
00:05:33,159 --> 00:05:34,690
we found this near the body.

95
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:36,430
It might belong to the victim.

96
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:38,090
Let Physician Jiu take a look.

97
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:42,900
[Guangping County]

98
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:47,350
[Zhang Pu]

99
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:54,510
Why the long face?

100
00:05:54,909 --> 00:05:56,310
Still can't find a place?

101
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:59,409
It's so hard.

102
00:06:01,370 --> 00:06:03,460
With my parents here,

103
00:06:03,490 --> 00:06:04,740
there's no spare room at my place

104
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:05,620
for you to stay.

105
00:06:06,110 --> 00:06:07,550
The houses available now

106
00:06:07,950 --> 00:06:08,750
are either too remote,

107
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:09,580
too run-down,

108
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,070
or too expensive.

109
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:12,480
Seriously,

110
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,190
Guangping is a vast city

111
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,770
with so many houses.

112
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,860
Are they all taken?

113
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:18,600
Is there not one

114
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,190
that I can rent for cheap?

115
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:22,480
I'm young

116
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:24,480
and working hard to save money,

117
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,020
but how come I can't even afford

118
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:27,970
to rent a house?

119
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,560
Don't stress.

120
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,830
It happens that

121
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,560
I've got

122
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,960
nothing to do these days.

123
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,159
I'll help you look.

124
00:06:40,130 --> 00:06:40,930
Have some too.

125
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:43,430
No, thank you.

126
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,370
I've gained weight from not working for days.

127
00:06:45,370 --> 00:06:47,030
My manager told me to cut back.

128
00:06:47,620 --> 00:06:48,950
I'll just watch you eat.

129
00:06:49,590 --> 00:06:50,220
Alright.

130
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,340
My Lady.

131
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:04,840
-Where are you going?
-Banxia!

132
00:07:06,190 --> 00:07:07,150
The victim, Zhang Pu,

133
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:08,080
was 40 years old.

134
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,630
Years ago, he bought himself a position

135
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:11,180
at the government office

136
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,440
as a market inspector.

137
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:14,090
He was a heavy drinker,

138
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,040
bad-tempered,

139
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:16,390
and often skipped work.

140
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:17,120
Over time,

141
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:18,390
his colleagues

142
00:07:18,390 --> 00:07:19,920
acted as if he didn't exist.

143
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:20,830
His last check-in

144
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:21,890
was half a year ago.

145
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,040
After that, no one

146
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,100
ever saw him again.

147
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,320
No one looked for him?

148
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,920
Market inspection is a cushy job—

149
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,680
just helping manage

150
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,680
street vendors for the government.

151
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,430
He paid

152
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:34,630
for the post,

153
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:35,310
and his superiors

154
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:36,510
knew what he was like.

155
00:07:36,830 --> 00:07:38,280
After failing to find him a few times,

156
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,280
they just gave up.

157
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,800
What about his family?

158
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:43,040
He was an only child.

159
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:44,530
His parents are deceased.

160
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,960
He had a wife named Xingxian,

161
00:07:47,010 --> 00:07:48,210
who lives right here.

162
00:07:51,620 --> 00:07:52,250
Here?

163
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,970
You really didn't have to come.

164
00:07:57,409 --> 00:07:59,270
I've got nothing else to do today.

165
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:00,990
Suit yourself.

166
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Who are you looking for?

167
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,330
Are you Zhang Pu's wife?

168
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:18,750
Yes.

169
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:23,100
I'm a constable.

170
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:27,950
My Lord.

171
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:31,410
Do you know where your husband

172
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,429
is now?

173
00:08:32,909 --> 00:08:36,190
[Xingxian]

174
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,950
Is something wrong?

175
00:08:35,770 --> 00:08:36,880
My husband has been

176
00:08:36,909 --> 00:08:38,039
gone for half a year.

177
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,539
If that's the case,

178
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:41,429
why didn't you report it?

179
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,030
Well, you see,

180
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,800
he's a heavy drinker

181
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:47,000
and often goes traveling with friends.

182
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,840
Sometimes, he'd be gone for three

183
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,700
to five months.

184
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,910
That's why I didn't report it.

185
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,480
May I ask, My Lord,

186
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,550
has something happened?

187
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:02,750
He's dead.

188
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:03,960
He...

189
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,660
He's dead?

190
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,080
Dead?

191
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:11,730
He drank himself to death?

192
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:13,630
This Zhang fellow

193
00:09:13,630 --> 00:09:15,080
was no good.

194
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,360
Drinking all day,

195
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,500
and when drunk,

196
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,600
he beat his wife.

197
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:20,130
I've said it before—

198
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:21,670
if he kept drinking like that,

199
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:23,550
he'd drink himself to death sooner or later.

200
00:09:23,550 --> 00:09:24,390
Did I ask you?

201
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:31,630
Xingxian,

202
00:09:32,270 --> 00:09:33,620
you must stay strong.

203
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,850
My condolences, madam.

204
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:39,240
Come to the government office within three days

205
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,240
to claim the body.

206
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:40,910
Yes.

207
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:42,490
You come with me.

208
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,610
[Lv Sanlang]

209
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,090
Multiple scrapes on the limbs,

210
00:10:26,420 --> 00:10:27,620
all recent injuries.

211
00:10:28,070 --> 00:10:29,390
Judging by the torn clothing,

212
00:10:29,390 --> 00:10:31,390
they were likely caused by the fall.

213
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,170
His neck is dislocated and broken.

214
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:46,170
No obvious signs of poisoning.

215
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,340
Silver needle.

216
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,330
Indeed, no poison.

217
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,480
The only fatal wound

218
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:05,710
is on the neck.

219
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,440
On such a sunny day,

220
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:11,210
he actually fell and broke his neck just walking.

221
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:17,150
What's wrong?

222
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:31,120
[Guangping Government]

223
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,570
That guy didn't die, did he?

224
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,360
Banxia.

225
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,080
Do you know that person?

226
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,440
No?

227
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:45,870
Then why did you follow him?

228
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:47,250
It felt like...

229
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,160
like you knew something would happen.

230
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:51,740
My Lady.

231
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,360
Did you see

232
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:54,560
the white crow again?

233
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,170
What white crow?

234
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:04,450
It's so eerie.

235
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,200
I'll tell you about it later.

236
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:22,600
Banxia,

237
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:24,740
did you really see

238
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:26,450
that white crow on Lv Sanlang?

239
00:12:27,780 --> 00:12:29,110
Is he really dead?

240
00:12:31,980 --> 00:12:33,460
If only I could've

241
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:34,150
warned him.

242
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:35,620
But I...

243
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,030
Banxia,

244
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,700
don't be upset.

245
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,270
It's not your fault.

246
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,690
If you blame yourself

247
00:12:44,790 --> 00:12:46,340
and feel sad about this,

248
00:12:46,650 --> 00:12:47,390
isn't that exactly

249
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:49,050
what that Mirror Demon wants?

250
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:51,080
Yeah.

251
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:52,720
We all know

252
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,980
you're kind by nature.

253
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,570
But the world is so vast,

254
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,030
and people die in accidents

255
00:12:57,030 --> 00:12:58,030
every single day.

256
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,930
You can't put all the blame

257
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,000
on yourself.

258
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,640
Yes, Banxia.

259
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,000
You once saved my life

260
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,460
because of the white crow.

261
00:13:05,990 --> 00:13:06,910
It's getting late.

262
00:13:06,910 --> 00:13:08,510
Head back and have some rest.

263
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,270
I need to go to Sifang Street

264
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:13,360
to take care of something.

265
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,360
I'll go with them.

266
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,050
If you leave,

267
00:13:16,050 --> 00:13:17,850
who will fill out today's forms?

268
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,360
You can't do it?

269
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,380
I can, I can.

270
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,400
It's just that

271
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:23,960
there are quite a few forms today.

272
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,320
If I made mistakes again,

273
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,750
you'd nag me tomorrow.

274
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:28,770
It'd raise your blood pressure.

275
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:32,060
My incompetent colleague

276
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:32,840
can't do without me.

277
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,440
Then I won't see you off.

278
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,360
Thank you, thank you.

279
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,220
Xuanye.

280
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,290
What was that guy's name?

281
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,270
Does he have

282
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:50,030
any family?

283
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,010
Still thinking about that?

284
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:57,800
Tingzhou.

285
00:13:58,550 --> 00:13:59,870
Are the two of them...

286
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:01,320
What?

287
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:02,750
You know.

288
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:08,680
Together?

289
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,120
Well,

290
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:12,200
I'm not sure about Physician Jiu,

291
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,150
but Miss Duan

292
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:14,000
does like him.

293
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,270
I knew it!

294
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,850
I thought something was off last time.

295
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,880
Physician Jiu!

296
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,270
I didn't mean

297
00:14:26,290 --> 00:14:27,960
to interrupt your conversation.

298
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:29,720
It's just that it's getting late,

299
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,850
and I'm a bit hungry.

